Angular Directives:
-------------------
Angular directives are classes to add extra functionality to the DOM.

we have different types of directives
1. Component - The component directive comes with template or template URLs that represent something in DOM.
2.Structural - NgIf, NgSwitch - Changes the structure of DOM
3.Attribute - NgStyle, NgClass -Changes the appearence of DOM

Note: The Component directive directly associated with the component where as structural and attribute directives are tailored with DOM manupulation.
